Print a user-visible message when kubelogin blocks on the token-cache flock.

Since v1.30 (int128/kubelogin#1126) the credential plugin takes an exclusive
lock on ~/.kube/cache/oidc-login/<hash>.lock before refresh/device-code auth.
Another kubectl (or a leftover kubelogin from a timed-out session) can hold that
lock for minutes while the user completes Dex login. Without feedback, kubectl
looks hung — the only hint is a V(1) log line ("acquiring the lock of token
cache") that never appears at default verbosity.

Upstream has known the class of problem since 2023 (int128/kubelogin#851, still
open) but only for the older auth-flow port lock, not this token-cache lock.

TryLock first; if another process holds the lock, emit one line on stderr, then
block as before.

--- a/pkg/tokencache/repository/repository.go	2026-06-28 19:56:03.085542933 -0700
+++ b/pkg/tokencache/repository/repository.go	2026-06-28 19:56:03.098449803 -0700
@@ -168,9 +168,16 @@
 	// https://github.com/int128/kubelogin/issues/1144
 	lockFilepath := filepath.Join(config.Directory, checksum+".lock")
 	lockFile := flock.New(lockFilepath)
-	if err := lockFile.Lock(); err != nil {
+	locked, err := lockFile.TryLock()
+	if err != nil {
 		return nil, fmt.Errorf("could not lock the cache file %s: %w", lockFilepath, err)
 	}
+	if !locked {
+		fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, "kubelogin: waiting for another login in progress (lock: %s)\n", lockFilepath)
+		if err := lockFile.Lock(); err != nil {
+			return nil, fmt.Errorf("could not lock the cache file %s: %w", lockFilepath, err)
+		}
+	}
 	return lockFile, nil
 }
 
